news.title: UP-RERA directs the promoters to file backlog of quarterly progress reports
news.para: Sanjay Bhoosreddy, chairman, UP-RERA said that while reviewing the progress of the projects, it was seen that many of the promoters are not filing the QPRs of their projects in time and some of them have filed the subsequent QPRs without filing the pending QPRs.

news.title: IDFC FIRST Bank leases 1.4 lakh sq ft in Bengaluru
news.para: The newly leased property has a total lease tenure of 9 years and commands a rental of Rs 135 per sqft, mentioned a registered lease document.

news.title: Bengaluru development body officials halt construction of illegal layout
news.para: Officials from the Bangalore Development Authority (BDA) office visited the alleged spot of illegal layout on January 11, 2023. The team visited Pattandur Agrahara Village, Whitefield took note of the construction work and put a temporary halt to it.

news.title: Pune civic body to publish list of notices to errant builders on website
news.para: Details about notices sent out regarding unauthorized real estate will be shared with the public through the Pune Municipal Corporation’s (PMC) official website.

news.title: Pune: Two high-value bungalows sealed at prime Camp spots
news.para: The properties fall under the Old Grant Bungalows (OGBs) category and are valued at over Rs100 crore in total as per the current market rate, a DEO official said.

news.title: Capacit'e Infra raises Rs 200 crore via QIP route
news.para: "Capacit'e Infraprojects announces the successful completion of its fundraise of Rs 200 crore through a QIP. The book was subscribed more than four times and witnessed traction from a diversified set of investors," it said.

news.title: UK builder Taylor Wimpey warns of tough market despite drop in mortgage rates
news.para: Britain's housing sector is hoping to see some relief as mortgage rates appear to have peaked with markets betting on Bank of England rate cuts later this year, but wider economic challenges have dented hopes of a robust recovery.

news.title: Maison Sia's founder buys luxury pad for Rs 116 crore in Mumbai’s Worli
news.para: The apartment spread over a massive 12,138 sq ft carpet area on the 49th floor of Three Sixty West is valued at around Rs 1 lakh per sq ft, pushing it higher in the tally of most expensive deals on per sq ft basis anywhere in the country.

news.title: South Korea to step up monitoring of real estate projects
news.para: There are lingering concerns over real estate projects, although financial markets have been stable since builder Taeyoung's Dec. 28 announcement to reschedule its debt, it said, after the minister's meeting with chiefs of the central bank and regulatory agencies.

news.title: Australia's Centuria Office REIT portfolio valuations dip 5.6%
news.para: The commercial real estate sector in Australia, particularly office and retail, is reeling under headwinds including a shortfall in demand owing to hybrid working arrangements, rising interest rates lowering portfolio valuations for companies alike, and a slowing economy.

news.title: Migsun Group sells retail space in Delhi to Dmart for Rs 108 crore
news.para: Dmart has bought the space at the project in sector 22, Rohini in Delhi, according to a statement. The retail space has been acquired for Rs 108 crore, the statement said.

news.title: Deloitte appointed liquidator of China builder Jiayuan International
news.para: In a Hong Kong Stock Exchange filing, Jiayuan said Hong Kong's High Court had approved the appointment of Deloitte.

news.title: Tamil Nadu plans to merge villages with urban local bodies by December
news.para: The move, however, has come in for criticism from AIADMK, which has warned that this would deprive village panchayats of financial support from Centre for housing, road and sanitation programmes and demanded a public hearing for consensus.

news.title: ED raids at 11 places of coloniser, aides in Bulandshahr
news.para: The ED initiated investigation based on 18 FIRs lodged by the UP Police against Sudhir, his wife and other associates. Sudhir, a listed land mafia, has also been booked under Gangster Act from Kotwali Dehat of Bulandshahr.

news.title: Bengaluru Namma Metro phase-III set to roll this year
news.para: With three corridors covering 81.12 km, Metro Corporation awaits approvals and funding for metro expansion. The first corridor proposed Metro connectivity from JP Nagar fourth phase to Kempapura (32.15 km) with 22 stations.

news.title: Pimpri Chinchwad civic body seizes 200 properties for tax default this fiscal
news.para: The civic body has also cut water connections of 17 residential and commercial properties during this period for failure to pay taxes despite notices and warnings issued to the owners.

news.title: Dehradun: Residents caught in clash of RWAs over power supply
news.para: ​They alleged that even though both projects are of the same builder, they are registered separately in RERA and two different RWAs are monitoring the residential complexes.

news.title: Sebi to auction 30 properties of six companies on February 13
news.para: The other companies whose properties will also be auctioned are Bishal group of companies, Purusattam Infotech Industries, NVD Solar Ltd, Sun Plant Business and Jivan Sathi Dream Projects.

news.title: SC gives go-ahead to Shimla development plan 2041
news.para: ​The top court passed the order while allowing the appeal of the state government against the stay imposed by the National Green Tribunal (NGT) on the proposed SDP and a ban on construction activities.

news.title: Ajmera Realty records 98% year-on-year rise in Q3 sales at Rs 253 crore
news.para: The developer sold 1,03,573 sq ft space in the December quarter, up 63% from a year ago. The 98% on-year growth in sales value is attributed to sustained interest in key projects, Ajmera Manhattan and Ajmera Eden in Mumbai, as well as projects in Bengaluru, the company said.
